The number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in Kenya has risen to 96,251 following 112 new positive cases from 3,327 samples, the Ministry of Health has said.
The new cases comprise 98 Kenyans and 14 foreigners, of whom 69 are male and 43 female.
The youngest is a three-year-old baby while the oldest is 84.



