At the same time, the death toll in the country from the pandemic now stands at 1,667 after two fatalities were reported in the last 24 hours, Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kagwe said on Wednesday in a statement to media houses.
National recoveries 
Mr Kagwe, on the other hand, reported 816 new recoveries, bringing the tally for national recoveries to 78,475.
From the latest recoveries, 798 are from the home-based care programme while 18 have been discharged from various hospitals across the country.



